===Etymology===
Literally: '''[[sacrifice]] [[month]]'''
*''Month of the Year:'' '''[[臘]][[月]]'''
**'''Previous:''' [[冬月]]
**'''Next:''' [[正月]]
Note: Any month in the Chinese calendar may be preceded or followed by an [[intercalary]] month, an irregular month inserted into the calendar to bring the [[lunar year]] in line with the solar year.

===Noun===
'''臘月'''
#{{archaic}}: traditional name for the twelfth of the twelve months of the [[Chinese calendar]], each beginning on a [[new moon]]. 

